-- CMHC Says 81% of Canadians Are `Comfortable' With Level of Mortgage Debt
-- Alexandre Deslongchamps
-- 2010-04-26T12:15:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/cmhc-says-81-of-canadians-are-comfortable-with-level-of-mortgage-debt.html

          
          
             Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp.
said today that 81 percent of recent homebuyers are
“comfortable” with the level of their mortgage debt.  
 The survey also found that more than two-thirds of
respondents plan to pay off their mortgage early. Government-
owned CMHC released the result of its survey of 2,500 active
mortgage users in an e-mailed statement.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexandre Deslongchamps in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        